Debra "Deb" Eschmeyer has been announced as the new Executive Director of Let's Move! and Senior Policy Advisor for Nutrition Policy at the White House. She will be taking over from Sam Kass, who left in December. Eschmeyer is known for her work in teaching children about healthy eating and has co-founded FoodCorps, a national AmeriCorps service program that focuses on improving food and nutrition in schools. She has received recognition for her efforts, including being named one of "The Most Innovative Women in Food and Drink" by Fortune and Food & Wine. Eschmeyer grew up on a dairy farm and also started a fruit and vegetable farm with her husband.